    {
        "content": "<p>Do we have the instance for <code>IsGalois ℚ ℂ</code> or <code>Normal ℚ ℂ</code>? I did not find it in mathlib :((</p>",
        "id": 448125336,
        "sender_full_name": "Edison Xie",
        "timestamp": 1719759947
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The extension is not algebraic, so cannot be Galois. The docstring for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsGalois#doc\">docs#IsGalois</a> says<br>\n\"A field extension E/F is Galois if it is both separable and normal. Note that in mathlib a separable extension of fields is by definition algebraic.\"</p>",
        "id": 448127288,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Stoll",
        "timestamp": 1719760893
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"479359\">Michael Stoll</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Galois.20Extension.20of.20C.20over.20Q/near/448127288\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The extension is not algebraic, so cannot be Galois. The docstring for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsGalois#doc\">docs#IsGalois</a> says<br>\n\"A field extension E/F is Galois if it is both separable and normal. Note that in mathlib a separable extension of fields is by definition algebraic.\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>huh?I thought every extension of a char zero field is separable?</p>",
        "id": 448131180,
        "sender_full_name": "Edison Xie",
        "timestamp": 1719762514
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Isn't Q a perfect field?</p>",
        "id": 448131189,
        "sender_full_name": "Edison Xie",
        "timestamp": 1719762524
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>\"Separable\" is defined in terms of a property of the minimal polynomials of the elements of the larger field over the smaller one, which requires the elements to be algebraic. <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb Q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8556em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span></span></span></span> being a perfect field means that every <em>algebraic</em> extension of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb Q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8556em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span></span></span></span> is separable.</p>",
